headline: 'The Five' on COVID mandates, Ukraine war and NATO

utterances.speaker: JESSE WATTERS, FOX NEWS HOST
utterances.sentences: The Supreme Court nomination hearing happening right now on Capitol Hill and we'll have more on that later. Hello, everybody. I'm Jesse Watters along with Judge Jeanine Pirro, Jessica Tarlov, Dana Perino, and Greg Gutfeld. It's five o'clock in New York City, and this is THE FIVE. President Biden touching down in Europe for an emergency meeting with NATO allies in an attempt to put more pressure on Vladimir Putin. Russia continuing its brutal assault on Ukraine but it comes with heavy losses. NATO's top commander now saying that Russia may have lost as many as 15,000 troops so far. Biden now fearful that a desperate Putin may escalate his attacks even further.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: What would you like to say to European partners?

utterances.speaker: JOE BIDEN, PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA
utterances.sentences: I'm going to say that to their face. I'm going to say all I have to say. I'm going to say when I get there.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: How concerned are you about the threat of chemical warfare right now, that Russia may use chemical weapons? How high is that threat?

utterances.speaker: BIDEN
utterances.sentences: I think it's a real threat.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: But the threats don't end there. Putin's own spokesman refusing to rule out using nuclear weapons against Ukrainian forces.

utterances.speaker: DMITRY PESKOV, KREMLIN SPOKESPERSON
utterances.sentences: We have a concept of domestic security. And, well, it's a public, you can read all the reasons for nuclear arms to be used. So, if it is an existential threat for our country, then it can be used in accordance with our concept.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Did you enjoy the president, Greg, coming out to the cameras and giving that statement?

utterances.speaker: GREG GUTFELD, FOX NEWS CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: You know, I can't answer that. I'm not an expert on war. I was channeling to Judge Jackson.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Very good.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes, I think it's fair -- I'm going to do that every block so I never have to prepare. You know what, I don't know what's going on. We need to have an expert here right now. Where is judge -- where is General Keane? First off, they are calling these emergency talks. Then why are they -- why were they -- why were they -- what happened three weeks ago? I mean, this was an emergency a long time ago. We waited so long it could have occurred before the war because we could see it coming. We knew there were problems. Those troops are amassing since April of last year. I'm going to go back to what I said before and you echoed it, which was Trump was pretty good at the stuff. I mean, we have examples from North Korea, even to Mexico trade talks, China, Canada. He knew that you don't do all carrots and you don't do all sticks. I don't know what the ratio is. I think it's like one stick to one carrot.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: No one knows.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: No one knows, but Trump always did, you know, he said the nice things and then he did the tough things. But you don't wait until a country is rubble and you have four million refugees, you know, out, you know, around, it's a sad state of affairs. I don't know. To think about the Russian side, we tend to rule things out, they don't rule things out. You know? That's their thing. But I don't have confidence in Joe. I don't think he has an original thought. He might -- he is good at saying good job to other people in the room but he can't just say, come on, man to Putin when he's not even there or he doesn't take your calls. So, I think the one thing he's got to say, this is when my expertise comes in, stick to one essential truth. The invasion was a clear violation of international law. Don't start talking about protecting liberal democracies because places like China and Russia they don't draw that line. It's not that important to them.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: But they do understand violation of international law. You can't get around that statement.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Borders.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Borders. Rights. Sovereign countries, blah, blah, blah and don't bring up regime change. Just say, you know, I think that would be a good start but I'm not an expert. I think we need to get an expert.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Dana, you are an expert.

utterances.speaker: DANA PERINO, FOX NEWS CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: I don't know, I'm not an expert either. And I don't know what's going to happen.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I don't know like cases are going to become -- become in front -- in front of the court so I can't answer anything.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Do you think he is going to go over there? You always talk about when you over and do these trips having deliverables. What will be the deliverables when he touches down and does this big meeting?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Well, one thing was, so when they were discussing the possibility and Poland wanted to send the MiGs to Ukraine to be able to use. That apparently was signed off by Blinken. Kamala Harris was going to go and make the announcement and it was going to happen and the night before or day and a half before, Biden changed his mind. Now that might be fine and we might look back and say he probably, maybe that was a good decision. But they sent her there was nothing and then she didn't have a great performance, but that's typical, so then she has nothing to say -- to deliver. It is interesting how he wants to be the leader of the free world, but he's also been in the backseat. He was dragged into the sanctions by Europe and by -- and then by Congress, right, on the oil part of this equation. So, what do they deliver here? If they can deliver some sort of way to say we have intelligence that says Putin is going to draw back and say that partial victory because they're not going to be in NATO. Is that a way to end things? OK, fine. If Ukraine says if that happens, we got to have some sort of security guarantee for our people so we can rebuild this place, can Biden to that? Yes, maybe, that might be something he could do. And then the other thing that they have to do is figure out a way to collect more intelligence on Putin's plans because that is actually been something that our intelligence community has done very well. Penetrated into the Kremlin and they are confused, they are not sure who is telling people what and so I will continue to try to drive that wedge if they can, I'm not talking about regime change but letting the generals know that, like we're on to you and you are losing these many people and it could even be more than that.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Do you think the Russians have little spies that are going to be scurrying around this NATO meeting, Judge?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Interesting.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Like the waiter?

utterances.speaker: JEANINE PIRRO, FOX NEWS CO-HOST
utterances.sentences: Well, that's what they --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: A Russian comes over with some Perrier, he's listening to everything?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Probably, that's what they do.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: That's what they do. But look, I saw pictures of Mariupol today. And it looks like it's completely devastated. And I couldn't help but think, and this is to Greg's point. You know, here we are four weeks into this. And now, all we've heard is Biden talk about the fact, they are going to use chemical weapons. There's going to be a cyberattack. There's going to be nuclear weapons. And it's all about what Putin is going to do. But then we say, look, we don't want to get involved. I understand that. We don't want to get involved, but at the same time, you could have been delivering a message of, hey, buddy, --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: -- we got the same things that you have. And pushback with, you know, we can do the same kind of thing. We've got offensive stuff to do too, as opposed to saying everybody, he's got all this stuff and you better run under your desk right away. And you know, when we're not looking, they are not looking to have us have boots on the ground, but I still don't understand. And the sad part is when I saw Mariupol today, why not the S-300, why not the Patriot? And someone said, I hosted Laura show last night, and someone said, well, you don't know, they may already have the Iron Dome there. And so, it doesn't look at --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: He'll have that.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: -- the place is being destroyed. And so now the demand and the final shoe that's going to drop is famine. Ukraine provides 40 percent of the world's wheat? We got four million refugees, there is no heat, no water, no food, no wheat, now what are we going to do? Go over there and just look at Putin, and say, gee, you know, he can't do this anymore? We got to provide money to rebuild, we've got to take care of the refugees. Maybe a world global famine now out in terms of food? And I keep going back to my thought which is this, get the NATO country to stand there with Zelenskyy with three leaders every day. Get the pope. If Pope Francis is upset about it, Pope, with all due respect, stand there with Zelenskyy. Get the Russian patriarch the great Orthodox Church, as well as the head of the great Orthodox Church. Have them all stand there in one place.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Part of me thinks that the west wants this proxy war to kill Russia finally because it doesn't look like they were making that big of an effort to cut a deal and make Putin leave and save any face whatsoever. It's all about sanctions and just grinding him down.

utterances.speaker: JESSICA TARLOV, FOX NEWS CONTRIBUTOR
utterances.sentences: I don't know. It seems like a pretty tremendous effort has been made. When you consider the fact that the Russians have lost 15,000 troops so far which is more than they lost in the war in Afghanistan. They have soldiers regularly turning themselves over to the Ukrainians. They're suffering from frostbite, they're frozen. They don't have the appropriate equipment to do this. The sanctions have been incredibly difficult, obviously for the everyday Russians but have hit a lot of these oligarchs who apparently turning left and right on Putin. There was a rumor I don't know if it has been confirmed yet, that one of his very high-ranking generals has actually turned around and said I'm not interested in this. And in terms of real on the ground deliverables, Jake Sullivan was briefing the press on the plane heading over to the NATO summit. He said that the U.S. is coming with more humanitarian aid which is something they desperately need, and also refugee assistance. And that's where I feel like the U.S. has dropped the ball in all of this. It's something insane like only 11 Ukrainian refugees have been allowed in since this war started. They're only basically letting people who were here before the war started stay. And that's a huge dereliction of duty. You cannot have what's going on with Poland, whether taking millions and millions and millions and not step up to the plate there. Calling it a war crime, big deal from Secretary Blinken today. And also, I wanted to mention that Madeleine Albright passed away today as well, which is incredibly sad event. I don't know, I was thinking of Blinken talking about war crimes and then Madeleine Albright have been through. Anyway, I think that we are doing a lot. And I think that the intricacies and how complicated this is to unite western countries, we all say we're united. We're all democracies. We are very different types of countries who get our gas, our oil, our food from very diverse places. And I think that Biden is doing a hell of a good job actually in keeping the wheels running on this. And we'll see what he says at NATO but the Ukrainians are getting a lot of help from us.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: We should send them to our southern border.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes, let them in.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Let them right across.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Let them right across and then we get them on the planes, right?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes. Give them some cash.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Fly them in --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I read this story last week that the Ukrainians that were there that went to the border were allowed -- were being allowed in and the Russians were not.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Jesus.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Very hypocritical. Straight ahead, it's the media Supreme Court protection plan. The press rushing to bash Republicans and praise Biden's nominee.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson back for another marathon round of questions today on Capitol Hill. Jackson being pressed by Lindsey Graham about her sentencing in child pornography cases.

utterances.speaker: SEN. LINDSEY GRAHAM (R-SC)
utterances.sentences: You think it is a bigger deterrent to take somebody who's on a computer looking at sexual images of children and the most disgusting way is to supervise their computer habits versus putting them in jail?

utterances.speaker: KETANJI BROWN JACKSON, U.S. SUPREME COURT NOMINEE
utterances.sentences: No, Senator, I didn't say versus.

utterances.speaker: GRAHAM
utterances.sentences: That's exactly what you said. I think the best way to deter people from getting on computer and viewing thousands and hundreds and overtime may be millions of a population of whole of children being exploited and abused every time somebody clicks on is to put their ass in jail.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: But don't worry the mainstream media has already rushed to Jackson's defense as lashing out at Republicans for daring to ask the judge questions about her own record.

utterances.speaker: JOY REID, HOST, MSNBC
utterances.sentences: The word I would use for Tom Cotton was thuggish. I thought Lindsey Graham was screaming and weird. Josh Hawley, ridiculous.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: I mean, quite frankly, it looked like I saw Ted Cruz commit a hate crime.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: That line of questioning which was so grotesque from Lindsey graham.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.sentences: Republican grievance signaling, RGS.

utterances.speaker: DON LEMON, HOST, CNN
utterances.sentences: It's amazing to watch someone who is a, quite frankly, an intellectual giant be questioned by people who have really no idea about the law.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: All right. So, you know what, I'll start with you, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: The judge in a further explanation of her going under the guidelines for child pornography said, you know, the fact that it's on the internet, which most judges would see it as an aggravating factor and the statute says you can consider it as an aggravating factor, she doesn't think it is. She said because, you know the statute was drafted before the internet. What I find so incredible is that she is so willing to look for every excuse she can to get out from under sentencing guidelines as it relates to child porn. And the more we dig into this, the more it's clear that she would rather have a probation officer check a guy on his computer than put him in jail when the guidelines recommend jail.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I would say she is soft on crime. Did I answer that question?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Thank you very much. I want to talk about Don Lemon referring to Judge Jackson as an intellectual giant. To be fair, compared to Don, a plastic garment bag just screaming in the wind isn't intellectual giant. Yet the media is so much in the tank for this candidate, they should wet suits and snorkels.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I like that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: But to be fair, this whole, this is how it works, right? There is a lot of grandstanding. One side of the media becomes the critics and the other side becomes their cheerleader. And then it switches and then, you know, we become nicer and they become angrier. But we were told by the media, that this would be a historic choice, right, after all she is a black woman. But how do you know that she is? The media, they are not biologists. We need to employ a biologist to check every historic choice that is based on identity. I have no idea if Judge Gorsuch is actually a white libertarian, do you? We have a Black female.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: It could be.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: We need a biologist to check the stuff.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: All right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I'm not a biologist.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: So, let me go right --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Jessica got to throw up --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Let me go right to Jessica with that. You know, I really thought that, you know, she ideologically, she first into the court, she's replacing Breyer. And then all of a sudden, she's asked by Senator Marsha Blackburn to define what it means to be a woman. And she basically said she can't. And then thinks, and she says, I'm not a biologist. What's the problem there?

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: Well, Marsha Blackburn was on earlier today with John Roberts and he asked her to answer her own question and she would say I am a woman. I am a female. Now, Judge Jackson certainly could have gotten that answer up. But that wasn't what she's after.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: But she didn't.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: But it wasn't what she was after. It was a got you question because she wanted to talk about Leah Thomas and she wanted to talk about trans athletes. And Judge Jackson, rightfully so, I believe did not want to get in the dirt and have that fight with people --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: How is that dirt?

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: How is --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: That maybe the case that they may decide? How is that dirt?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: And it's in the water.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: It's a squeaky-clean example. It was playing into Marsha Blackburn and the fact that she showed up and did not have a good answer prepared. Because I know that you would want more than that. What she wanted was Judge Jackson to say something about born biologically female, that someone who is born with a vagina, whether they then transition and become a man later in life, someone with a penis.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: But it's kind of interesting that she -- that Judge Jackson said we need -- I'm not biologist. Because is it about biology? I thought maybe it's not about biology. I thought that's what we were talking about. I mean, we all know what was going on there.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: And that --

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: And she didn't want her hearing to turn into screaming matches about the war culture points --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: So, we're going to give her -- we're going to give her credit for not answering a question?

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: I actually think that with the hearings that we have seen recently, yes, I want to give her credit for not degrading herself to having a fight about these woke culture battles, yes. I do want to give her credit for it because I have full confidence that Judge Jackson thinks that people who watch child porn are bad people and --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Well --

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: -- that she could muster and answer of I would say I'm a woman, I would say I'm a female.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes, but she didn't, and that's the problem. Because she didn't have the cajones obviously which is Geraldo can say --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Well, we should ask a biologist.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: I mean.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: I mean, and even child pornography, I think it's despicable but I'm going to go under whatever the prosecutor says, whatever the statute says.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: But she --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Because the internet wasn't there. Well, the internet was there. But Jesse, why don't you finish this up.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: If that's a got you question, what is -- are you are rapist? That seems like a got you question to me. She should have been able to answer that question, Jessica.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: Do you think anyone --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Anybody can answer that question smoothly. If she is that brilliant, spin it. Say, you know what, I was born a female because I have biological female parts but this is a complicated issue now in the United States of America and gender is influx because of this and that and the other thing. You're done and then that's how you scoot through.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: Next up is --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: The fact that she couldn't answer that question it makes me think maybe she's not as brilliant as everybody says she is because that's a slam-dunk question and everybody knows it. I also don't like this thing. The Democrats breathed fire at these Republican nominees, really nasty stuff. But someone ask her what the definition of a woman is and the media rushes in and starts giving chest compression, they were like, they're trying to save her from near death. These things are so stacked. You had Republican nominees accused of rape, sexual harassment, bigotry, racism, sexism, everything. And Democrats don't even give them like a little sympathy vote. All of these things are so over on the other side.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: It's crazy.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: All right, Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Well, I just wanted to add, I was going to make some media bias point but you did it so well. I am going to leave that there. I don't think that -- I don't think that they prepared well enough for this child porn issue on the Democratic side or at the White House when they were doing the mock hearings. I don't think they saw it coming and I don't think they're handled it all that well. I think that there are a lot of people who say obviously this is ridiculous and the Republicans are blowing this out of proportion. However, parents aren't going to see it that way. They're not going to hear it that way and parental involvement in their children's lives is the a, number one issue in all of these swing districts and the swing states. So, let's just say you're in a tough district and you thought you were going to run on the fact that Joe Biden had just nominated and confirmed to the Supreme Court the first black woman and this is going to be something to be celebrated. It is. However, you also know you are going to have to take a tough vote because now you are going to be labeled as soft on crime just like Judge Jackson. That's how those ads are going to run and this is going to play well into the midterms.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Well said, well said. All right. Next, Democrats are following the political science in changing their tune on COVID mandates.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Warnings of a red wave seemed to have scared the White House into shifting its COVID messaging. The administration planning to no longer look at cases when recommending masks, and will instead focus on hospitalizations and deaths. And to no one surprise, the party seems to be pivoting against the mandates that they once championed. The Dem in charge of midterm messaging now saying it's completely over mask mandates. And comedian Bill Maher warning that his party, the Democrats have gone too far.

utterances.speaker: BILL MAHER, COMEDIAN
utterances.sentences: California has got to get its arms around this issue. I mean it just does. What, first of all, we know there has been exodus from this day and that's part because of high taxes and it's partly because piracies and it's all year around, but it's also because people can't (muted) do anything.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Jesse, Bill Maher sounding more and more like me, which I'm OK with.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: He influenced me, now I'm influencing him.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: You think so?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: This all come full circle.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Has it?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes, we go to bed and breakfast now and against. That's all right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: OK. Do you go to bed?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: No.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: And breakfast.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Yes, after breakfast.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: I get nervous about something --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: What?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: -- when we say the word red wave.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: I know.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Let's not say that.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: Let's not jinx ourselves, ourselves.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.sentences: I'm not part of your group.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: So even the airlines aren't taking mask that seriously anymore. I flew to Florida and back over the weekend. I didn't even have a mask to get down there. I had to ask Johnny to get me a mask. So I had one of my pocket, I get to JFK, and I don't even put it on. That's my new thing. I don't put it on until someone tells me to put it on. And no one told me to put it on until we actually boarded the plane. So I kind of was putting mine on and Emma didn't put it on at all. Not very compliant. And she was scolded, but gently. And then when we sat down, we put it on for takeoff. And then we, you know, you nibble it your peanuts, and you take your drink, and that's the scam and they don't remind you the whole flight.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.sentences: Why are you telling me that's a scam.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: No, I've mentioned the scam before. So I trashed it when I get to Fort Myers and then you're good for the rest. So I'm back in Fort Myers on the return trip. I find that it's all crinkled up in my pocket. I don't put it on, until I get on the flight. I did put it on for the Delta lounge because I wanted to make a good impression. But when I get onto the flight JetBlue was a little bit more persnickety. They are and it wasn't a personal announcement. It was the over the intercom announcement. I felt I was being targeted because I was in the first row and they saw me but again, you put it on then you cheat with the peanuts and then you throw it away when you land in JFK. This thing is over.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.sentences: Do you know what I love? I love laugh -- I love laughing at people who are leaving a flight and leaving the airport with their mask on. You can take it off the moment -- the moment the doors open and take it off because what are they going to do? Kick you out? You won't be right. So that's means 50%, 50% of the people in the airport do not have to wear masks because they're leaving. They get off for God's sake.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: So used to wear it all the time. I agree with you. I think JetBlue is a lot more persnickety.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.sentences: They are.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.sentences: But Delta is wonderful about it.

utterances.utterance: I don't know, I'm not an expert either. And I don't know what's going to happen.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I don't know like cases are going to become -- become in front -- in front of the court so I can't answer anything.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Do you think he is going to go over there? You always talk about when you over and do these trips having deliverables. What will be the deliverables when he touches down and does this big meeting?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, one thing was, so when they were discussing the possibility and Poland wanted to send the MiGs to Ukraine to be able to use. That apparently was signed off by Blinken. Kamala Harris was going to go and make the announcement and it was going to happen and the night before or day and a half before, Biden changed his mind. Now that might be fine and we might look back and say he probably, maybe that was a good decision. But they sent her there was nothing and then she didn't have a great performance, but that's typical, so then she has nothing to say -- to deliver. It is interesting how he wants to be the leader of the free world, but he's also been in the backseat. He was dragged into the sanctions by Europe and by -- and then by Congress, right, on the oil part of this equation. So, what do they deliver here? If they can deliver some sort of way to say we have intelligence that says Putin is going to draw back and say that partial victory because they're not going to be in NATO. Is that a way to end things? OK, fine. If Ukraine says if that happens, we got to have some sort of security guarantee for our people so we can rebuild this place, can Biden to that? Yes, maybe, that might be something he could do. And then the other thing that they have to do is figure out a way to collect more intelligence on Putin's plans because that is actually been something that our intelligence community has done very well. Penetrated into the Kremlin and they are confused, they are not sure who is telling people what and so I will continue to try to drive that wedge if they can, I'm not talking about regime change but letting the generals know that, like we're on to you and you are losing these many people and it could even be more than that.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Do you think the Russians have little spies that are going to be scurrying around this NATO meeting, Judge?

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Interesting.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Like the waiter?

utterances.speaker: JEANINE PIRRO, FOX NEWS CO-HOST
utterances.utterance: Well, that's what they --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: A Russian comes over with some Perrier, he's listening to everything?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Probably, that's what they do.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: That's what they do. But look, I saw pictures of Mariupol today. And it looks like it's completely devastated. And I couldn't help but think, and this is to Greg's point. You know, here we are four weeks into this. And now, all we've heard is Biden talk about the fact, they are going to use chemical weapons. There's going to be a cyberattack. There's going to be nuclear weapons. And it's all about what Putin is going to do. But then we say, look, we don't want to get involved. I understand that. We don't want to get involved, but at the same time, you could have been delivering a message of, hey, buddy, --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: -- we got the same things that you have. And pushback with, you know, we can do the same kind of thing. We've got offensive stuff to do too, as opposed to saying everybody, he's got all this stuff and you better run under your desk right away. And you know, when we're not looking, they are not looking to have us have boots on the ground, but I still don't understand. And the sad part is when I saw Mariupol today, why not the S-300, why not the Patriot? And someone said, I hosted Laura show last night, and someone said, well, you don't know, they may already have the Iron Dome there. And so, it doesn't look at --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: He'll have that.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: -- the place is being destroyed. And so now the demand and the final shoe that's going to drop is famine. Ukraine provides 40 percent of the world's wheat? We got four million refugees, there is no heat, no water, no food, no wheat, now what are we going to do? Go over there and just look at Putin, and say, gee, you know, he can't do this anymore? We got to provide money to rebuild, we've got to take care of the refugees. Maybe a world global famine now out in terms of food? And I keep going back to my thought which is this, get the NATO country to stand there with Zelenskyy with three leaders every day. Get the pope. If Pope Francis is upset about it, Pope, with all due respect, stand there with Zelenskyy. Get the Russian patriarch the great Orthodox Church, as well as the head of the great Orthodox Church. Have them all stand there in one place.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Part of me thinks that the west wants this proxy war to kill Russia finally because it doesn't look like they were making that big of an effort to cut a deal and make Putin leave and save any face whatsoever. It's all about sanctions and just grinding him down.

utterances.speaker: JESSICA TARLOV, FOX NEWS CONTRIBUTOR
utterances.utterance: I don't know. It seems like a pretty tremendous effort has been made. When you consider the fact that the Russians have lost 15,000 troops so far which is more than they lost in the war in Afghanistan. They have soldiers regularly turning themselves over to the Ukrainians. They're suffering from frostbite, they're frozen. They don't have the appropriate equipment to do this. The sanctions have been incredibly difficult, obviously for the everyday Russians but have hit a lot of these oligarchs who apparently turning left and right on Putin. There was a rumor I don't know if it has been confirmed yet, that one of his very high-ranking generals has actually turned around and said I'm not interested in this. And in terms of real on the ground deliverables, Jake Sullivan was briefing the press on the plane heading over to the NATO summit. He said that the U.S. is coming with more humanitarian aid which is something they desperately need, and also refugee assistance. And that's where I feel like the U.S. has dropped the ball in all of this. It's something insane like only 11 Ukrainian refugees have been allowed in since this war started. They're only basically letting people who were here before the war started stay. And that's a huge dereliction of duty. You cannot have what's going on with Poland, whether taking millions and millions and millions and not step up to the plate there. Calling it a war crime, big deal from Secretary Blinken today. And also, I wanted to mention that Madeleine Albright passed away today as well, which is incredibly sad event. I don't know, I was thinking of Blinken talking about war crimes and then Madeleine Albright have been through. Anyway, I think that we are doing a lot. And I think that the intricacies and how complicated this is to unite western countries, we all say we're united. We're all democracies. We are very different types of countries who get our gas, our oil, our food from very diverse places. And I think that Biden is doing a hell of a good job actually in keeping the wheels running on this. And we'll see what he says at NATO but the Ukrainians are getting a lot of help from us.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: We should send them to our southern border.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes, let them in.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Let them right across.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Let them right across and then we get them on the planes, right?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes. Give them some cash.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Fly them in --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I read this story last week that the Ukrainians that were there that went to the border were allowed -- were being allowed in and the Russians were not.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Jesus.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Very hypocritical. Straight ahead, it's the media Supreme Court protection plan. The press rushing to bash Republicans and praise Biden's nominee.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson back for another marathon round of questions today on Capitol Hill. Jackson being pressed by Lindsey Graham about her sentencing in child pornography cases.

utterances.speaker: SEN. LINDSEY GRAHAM (R-SC)
utterances.utterance: You think it is a bigger deterrent to take somebody who's on a computer looking at sexual images of children and the most disgusting way is to supervise their computer habits versus putting them in jail?

utterances.speaker: KETANJI BROWN JACKSON, U.S. SUPREME COURT NOMINEE
utterances.utterance: No, Senator, I didn't say versus.

utterances.speaker: GRAHAM
utterances.utterance: That's exactly what you said. I think the best way to deter people from getting on computer and viewing thousands and hundreds and overtime may be millions of a population of whole of children being exploited and abused every time somebody clicks on is to put their ass in jail.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: But don't worry the mainstream media has already rushed to Jackson's defense as lashing out at Republicans for daring to ask the judge questions about her own record.

utterances.speaker: JOY REID, HOST, MSNBC
utterances.utterance: The word I would use for Tom Cotton was thuggish. I thought Lindsey Graham was screaming and weird. Josh Hawley, ridiculous.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.utterance: I mean, quite frankly, it looked like I saw Ted Cruz commit a hate crime.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.utterance: That line of questioning which was so grotesque from Lindsey graham.

utterances.speaker: UNKNOWN
utterances.utterance: Republican grievance signaling, RGS.

utterances.speaker: DON LEMON, HOST, CNN
utterances.utterance: It's amazing to watch someone who is a, quite frankly, an intellectual giant be questioned by people who have really no idea about the law.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: All right. So, you know what, I'll start with you, Greg.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: The judge in a further explanation of her going under the guidelines for child pornography said, you know, the fact that it's on the internet, which most judges would see it as an aggravating factor and the statute says you can consider it as an aggravating factor, she doesn't think it is. She said because, you know the statute was drafted before the internet. What I find so incredible is that she is so willing to look for every excuse she can to get out from under sentencing guidelines as it relates to child porn. And the more we dig into this, the more it's clear that she would rather have a probation officer check a guy on his computer than put him in jail when the guidelines recommend jail.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I would say she is soft on crime. Did I answer that question?

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Thank you very much. I want to talk about Don Lemon referring to Judge Jackson as an intellectual giant. To be fair, compared to Don, a plastic garment bag just screaming in the wind isn't intellectual giant. Yet the media is so much in the tank for this candidate, they should wet suits and snorkels.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I like that.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: But to be fair, this whole, this is how it works, right? There is a lot of grandstanding. One side of the media becomes the critics and the other side becomes their cheerleader. And then it switches and then, you know, we become nicer and they become angrier. But we were told by the media, that this would be a historic choice, right, after all she is a black woman. But how do you know that she is? The media, they are not biologists. We need to employ a biologist to check every historic choice that is based on identity. I have no idea if Judge Gorsuch is actually a white libertarian, do you? We have a Black female.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: It could be.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: We need a biologist to check the stuff.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: All right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I'm not a biologist.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: So, let me go right --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Jessica got to throw up --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Let me go right to Jessica with that. You know, I really thought that, you know, she ideologically, she first into the court, she's replacing Breyer. What's the problem there?

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: Well, Marsha Blackburn was on earlier today with John Roberts and he asked her to answer her own question and she would say I am a woman. I am a female. Now, Judge Jackson certainly could have gotten that answer up. But that wasn't what she's after.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: But she didn't.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: But it wasn't what she was after. It was a got you question because she wanted to talk about Leah Thomas and she wanted to talk about trans athletes. And Judge Jackson, rightfully so, I believe did not want to get in the dirt and have that fight with people --

utterances.utterance: How is that dirt?

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: How is --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: That maybe the case that they may decide? How is that dirt?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: And it's in the water.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: It's a squeaky-clean example. It was playing into Marsha Blackburn and the fact that she showed up and did not have a good answer prepared. Because I know that you would want more than that. What she wanted was Judge Jackson to say something about born biologically female, that someone who is born with a vagina, whether they then transition and become a man later in life, someone with a penis.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: But it's kind of interesting that she -- that Judge Jackson said we need -- I'm not biologist. Because is it about biology? I thought maybe it's not about biology. I thought that's what we were talking about. I mean, we all know what was going on there.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: And that --

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: And she didn't want her hearing to turn into screaming matches about the war culture points --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: So, we're going to give her -- we're going to give her credit for not answering a question?

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: I actually think that with the hearings that we have seen recently, yes, I want to give her credit for not degrading herself to having a fight about these woke culture battles, yes. I do want to give her credit for it because I have full confidence that Judge Jackson thinks that people who watch child porn are bad people and --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Well --

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: -- that she could muster and answer of I would say I'm a woman, I would say I'm a female.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes, but she didn't, and that's the problem. Because she didn't have the cajones obviously which is Geraldo can say --

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, we should ask a biologist.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: I mean.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: I mean, and even child pornography, I think it's despicable but I'm going to go under whatever the prosecutor says, whatever the statute says.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: But she --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Because the internet wasn't there. Well, the internet was there. But Jesse, why don't you finish this up.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: If that's a got you question, what is -- are you are rapist? That seems like a got you question to me. She should have been able to answer that question, Jessica.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: Do you think anyone --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Anybody can answer that question smoothly. If she is that brilliant, spin it. Say, you know what, I was born a female because I have biological female parts but this is a complicated issue now in the United States of America and gender is influx because of this and that and the other thing. You're done and then that's how you scoot through.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: Next up is --

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: The fact that she couldn't answer that question it makes me think maybe she's not as brilliant as everybody says she is because that's a slam-dunk question and everybody knows it. I also don't like this thing. The Democrats breathed fire at these Republican nominees, really nasty stuff. But someone ask her what the definition of a woman is and the media rushes in and starts giving chest compression, they were like, they're trying to save her from near death. These things are so stacked. You had Republican nominees accused of rape, sexual harassment, bigotry, racism, sexism, everything. And Democrats don't even give them like a little sympathy vote. All of these things are so over on the other side.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: It's crazy.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: All right, Dana.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Well, I just wanted to add, I was going to make some media bias point but you did it so well. I am going to leave that there. I don't think that -- I don't think that they prepared well enough for this child porn issue on the Democratic side or at the White House when they were doing the mock hearings. I don't think they saw it coming and I don't think they're handled it all that well. I think that there are a lot of people who say obviously this is ridiculous and the Republicans are blowing this out of proportion. However, parents aren't going to see it that way. They're not going to hear it that way and parental involvement in their children's lives is the a, number one issue in all of these swing districts and the swing states. So, let's just say you're in a tough district and you thought you were going to run on the fact that Joe Biden had just nominated and confirmed to the Supreme Court the first black woman and this is going to be something to be celebrated. It is. However, you also know you are going to have to take a tough vote because now you are going to be labeled as soft on crime just like Judge Jackson. That's how those ads are going to run and this is going to play well into the midterms.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Well said, well said. All right. Next, Democrats are following the political science in changing their tune on COVID mandates.

utterances.utterance: Warnings of a red wave seemed to have scared the White House into shifting its COVID messaging. utterances.utterance: California has got to get its arms around this issue. I mean it just does. utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Jesse, Bill Maher sounding more and more like me, which I'm OK with.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: He influenced me, now I'm influencing him.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: You think so?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: This all come full circle.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Has it?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, we go to bed and breakfast now and against. That's all right.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: OK. Do you go to bed?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: No.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: And breakfast.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes, after breakfast.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: I get nervous about something --

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: What?

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: -- when we say the word red wave.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I know.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Let's not say that.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: Let's not jinx ourselves, ourselves.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: I'm not part of your group.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: So even the airlines aren't taking mask that seriously anymore. I flew to Florida and back over the weekend. I didn't even have a mask to get down there. I had to ask Johnny to get me a mask. So I had one of my pocket, I get to JFK, and I don't even put it on. That's my new thing. I don't put it on until someone tells me to put it on. And no one told me to put it on until we actually boarded the plane. So I kind of was putting mine on and Emma didn't put it on at all. Not very compliant. And she was scolded, but gently. And then when we sat down, we put it on for takeoff. And then we, you know, you nibble it your peanuts, and you take your drink, and that's the scam and they don't remind you the whole flight.

utterances.speaker: PERINO
utterances.utterance: Why are you telling me that's a scam.

utterances.speaker: WATTERS
utterances.utterance: No, I've mentioned the scam before. So I trashed it when I get to Fort Myers and then you're good for the rest. So I'm back in Fort Myers on the return trip. utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Do you know what I love? I love laugh -- I love laughing at people who are leaving a flight and leaving the airport with their mask on. So that's means 50%, 50% of the people in the airport do not have to wear masks because they're leaving. They get off for God's sake.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: So used to wear it all the time. I agree with you. I think JetBlue is a lot more persnickety.

utterances.utterance: They are.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: But Delta is wonderful about it.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: I disagree. Delta -- I had a flight attendant that was a complete prison guard.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Well, that -- prison guard?

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yes.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: Well, maybe she knew you from your other line.

utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: That's true. I smuggled in a lot of things.

utterances.utterance: OK. You know what, you know, what's crazy about this? I just want to say one thing. Like, three months ago, if we didn't have a mask on, we were killing granny, right? utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: Yeah, it's true. You know, Jessica, that's the problem. I've said it before. It's got to be weird to be at a party that only makes choices based on the political ramifications, as opposed to right and wrong, Jessica. You should be ashamed of yourself.

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: Yes, Democrats are the only ones who want to win elections at any cost. But the person I think has been the most interesting on this is the governor, the Democratic governor of Colorado, Jared Polis, because after the first wave of mask mandates went away, he never brought them back. And then they had basically equal numbers of problematic cases as New Mexico. And he just said, there's your evidence for you where --

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: It doesn't work?

utterances.speaker: TARLOV
utterances.utterance: It doesn't. I think that it did -- it did work. And I don't want to say that what people did at the beginning when we didn't have a vaccine for this. utterances.speaker: GUTFELD
utterances.utterance: How dare, yes. By the way. I mean, we've been talking about this forever, Dana, that it should have been about hospitalizations and deaths, you know, and we're still asking little kids in New York.

utterances.speaker: PIRRO
utterances.utterance: This is an outrage. It is outrage.
